content:
Einstein Discovery in Tableau is supported in Tableau version 21.1 or later. Integration requires the appropriate license and user account setup.

License Requirements and Scope

To access Einstein Discovery functionality in Tableau, one of the following licenses must be provisioned in your Salesforce org:

* Einstein Discovery in Tableau license: get predictions
* CRM Analytics Plus license: get predictions, build, deploy, and manage models
* Einstein Predictions license: get predictions, build, deploy, and manage models

Salesforce User Accounts

You need a Salesforce account that is configured to access Einstein Discovery.

Einstein Discovery in Tableau License Requirements

If you use the Einstein Discovery in Tableau license, then your user account must have the View Einstein Discovery Recommendations Via Connect API system permission assigned to it.

CRM Analytics Plus license or Einstein Predictions License Requirements

* To get predictions using already deployed Einstein Discovery predictions, the account must have the View Einstein Discovery Recommendations system permission assigned to it.
* To build, deploy, and manage predictions in Einstein Discovery, the account must have one of the following permissions assigned to it: Manage Einstein Discovery, Create and Update Einstein Discovery Models, or Can Deploy and Manage Einstein Discovery Predictions.

For Salesforce user account configuration instructions, see Set Up Einstein Discovery.
title: Prerequisites for Einstein Discovery in Tableau
